01:28:30.580 --> 01:28:32.990
Or if you want to
make an iOS app,

01:28:32.990 --> 01:28:39.500
you'll probably compile it to
the [? XCode ?] Objective-C,

01:28:39.500 --> 01:28:40.660
and then compile that.

01:28:40.660 --> 01:28:43.070
But basically, it tries to
be all things to all people.

01:28:43.070 --> 01:28:44.552
Which is really
kind of dangerous.

01:28:44.552 --> 01:28:46.760
But hopefully, for the kind
of smallish project we're

01:28:46.760 --> 01:28:48.370
talking about, that'll be find.

01:28:48.370 --> 01:28:51.850
I call that one a noose,
because we haven't used it much.

01:28:51.850 --> 01:28:55.370
But it has all the simplicity of
Flixel for the Haxe Flixel game

01:28:55.370 --> 01:28:55.870
engine.

01:28:55.870 --> 01:28:58.274
So that is a good thing.

01:28:58.274 --> 01:29:00.190
