01:38:57.410 --> 01:39:00.520
So first off, what do we
mean by meaningful decisions?

01:39:00.520 --> 01:39:02.500
This is what I
mean when I say it.

01:39:02.500 --> 01:39:04.110
There's other
definitions out there.

01:39:04.110 --> 01:39:06.290
But this is the bare minimum.

01:39:06.290 --> 01:39:07.370
It should do this.

01:39:07.370 --> 01:39:09.040
It should have this.

01:39:09.040 --> 01:39:13.480
So three things-- any decision
a player makes in a game

01:39:13.480 --> 01:39:17.470
has an effect on the
game's overall state.

01:39:17.470 --> 01:39:18.840
So I make a decision.

01:39:18.840 --> 01:39:20.494
Something changed.

01:39:20.494 --> 01:39:22.410
Not only did something
change, but that change

01:39:22.410 --> 01:39:25.420
ripples through the
systems within the game.

01:39:25.420 --> 01:39:27.000
It affects the
entire game state,

01:39:27.000 --> 01:39:31.220
the entire game world-- not
just what the player might have,

01:39:31.220 --> 01:39:33.120
not just the
player's performance,

01:39:33.120 --> 01:39:35.180
not just the player's abilities.

01:39:35.180 --> 01:39:37.880
So a jump in these
games-- it can

01:39:37.880 --> 01:39:39.340
be meaningful in some games.

01:39:39.340 --> 01:39:42.960
But for this particular game
and this particular use,

01:39:42.960 --> 01:39:47.166
if the jump affects everything
else in the game in some form,

01:39:47.166 --> 01:39:48.290
that was really meaningful.

01:39:48.290 --> 01:39:50.244
And I'd be surprised
to see a jump do that.

01:39:50.244 --> 01:39:51.160
But it probably isn't.

01:39:51.160 --> 01:39:54.637
It's probably just a way
to get over an obstacle.

01:39:54.637 --> 01:39:55.720
So there's something else.

01:39:55.720 --> 01:39:58.095
There's some other kind of
decision a player has to make,

01:39:58.095 --> 01:40:02.220
rather than just that
one small decision.

01:40:02.220 --> 01:40:04.249
Third-- there should be
sufficient feedback--

01:40:04.249 --> 01:40:06.540
and we'll talk about feedback
later on and what exactly

01:40:06.540 --> 01:40:11.440
we mean by that-- that lets
the player be aware that they

01:40:11.440 --> 01:40:12.290
made that decision.

01:40:12.290 --> 01:40:13.660
Not only did I make
a decision, but I

01:40:13.660 --> 01:40:14.830
knew that I made a decision.

01:40:14.830 --> 01:40:16.400
There was something
that happened

01:40:16.400 --> 01:40:18.670
in the game that prompted
me to make that decision.

01:40:18.670 --> 01:40:20.506
And I actively
made the decision.

01:40:20.506 --> 01:40:22.130
I made the choice to
make the decision.

01:40:22.130 --> 01:40:23.750
I know I made the decision.

01:40:23.750 --> 01:40:28.820
And I actually see all those
effects happen in some form.

01:40:28.820 --> 01:40:31.450
At the bare minimum,
I make a decision.

01:40:31.450 --> 01:40:32.950
I see some short-term effects.

01:40:32.950 --> 01:40:35.650
There might be long-term effects
that I don't see right now,

01:40:35.650 --> 01:40:37.964
but I will have the
opportunity to see later.

01:40:37.964 --> 01:40:39.380
That's a little
bit more advanced.

