II, where there's

01:52:00.760 --> 01:52:02.050
one real strategy to the game.

01:52:02.050 --> 01:52:04.809
And that's just build a
city every three hexes.

01:52:04.809 --> 01:52:05.850
That's just how it works.

01:52:05.850 --> 01:52:08.681
And in the later games, they
tried to introduce some nuance

01:52:08.681 --> 01:52:09.180
to that.

01:52:12.545 --> 01:52:16.204
And again, I'm mixing
strategy and tactics

01:52:16.204 --> 01:52:17.370
as we're talking about this.

01:52:17.370 --> 01:52:18.880
They all go hand in hand.

01:52:18.880 --> 01:52:21.300
A lot of the games
that we've played,

01:52:21.300 --> 01:52:24.510
and that are these strategy
games that you talked about,

01:52:24.510 --> 01:52:26.270
are actually more
tactical games.

01:52:26.270 --> 01:52:29.810
There's much more emphasis
placed on the short-term thing

01:52:29.810 --> 01:52:31.969
I do now than the long term.

01:52:31.969 --> 01:52:34.260
That's not to say there isn't
long term in these games.

01:52:34.260 --> 01:52:38.375
If anybody's played
League of Legends,

01:52:38.375 --> 01:52:43.940
the metagame about the pick
process, so what champ to pick

01:52:43.940 --> 01:52:45.110
or not.

01:52:45.110 --> 01:52:47.150
That's a strategic maneuver.

01:52:47.150 --> 01:52:48.890
You're planning for
a long-term strategy

01:52:48.890 --> 01:52:51.029
that you're going to
play out within the game.

01:52:51.029 --> 01:52:52.570
And not only are
you planning for it.

01:52:52.570 --> 01:52:54.444
You picked it, and then
you're stuck with it.

01:52:54.444 --> 01:52:56.620
So those decisions last.

01:52:56.620 --> 01:52:58.079
With StarCraft II
it's build order,

01:52:58.079 --> 01:52:59.745
which can be a little
bit more flexible.

01:52:59.745 --> 01:53:01.360
There are build
orders that you can--

01:53:01.360 --> 01:53:03.580
that's build order
in that you are

01:53:03.580 --> 01:53:08.960
building units and buildings
and upgrades in the right order,

01:53:08.960 --> 01:53:11.530
such that you're prepared for
multiple different strategies

01:53:11.530 --> 01:53:12.560
coming into them.

01:53:12.560 --> 01:53:13.851
And I could be butchering that.

01:53:13.851 --> 01:53:14.547
I'm not a

01:53:14.547 --> 01:53:16.588
PHILLIP TAN: That's
definitely a good [INAUDIBLE]

01:53:16.588 --> 01:53:17.569
RIK EBERHARDT: Cool.

01:53:17.569 --> 01:53:18.610
But that's more flexible.

01:53:18.610 --> 01:53:21.000
Because I actually have
time within the game

01:53:21.000 --> 01:53:24.440
to make some tactical changes
to that long-term strategy

01:53:24.440 --> 01:53:25.909
that I decided on early.

01:53:25.909 --> 01:53:27.450
Unless you're playing
professionally.

01:53:27.450 --> 01:53:28.340
And then I've just
seem that they just

